description.0: The return...of TYPEFACE! Wait, who? You mean you don't remember Typeface? Well, that doesn't matter. He's back, and he wants REVENGE on Spidey! And who is the mysterious figure known as...Spellcheck?
description.1: The Thing faces off against the Kree who has turned Istvan against him! Ben is invited to join the freak show - will he say yes?
description.2: DEATH OF THE BLACK PANTHER PART 2 The King of Wakanda is facing his most pervasive foe yet- his own mortality. Will T'Challa overcome when his sanity starts to slip? And what should happen to his nation if they lose their king?
description.3: A Midtown High student pens an amorous letter to May Parker...anonymously.
description.4: The team has split and gone its separate ways, despite Guy Smith's honest effort to keep them together! After a shocking discovery, can Mister Sensitive enter the battle as a solo act?
description.6: Wolverine rescues a small girl from certain peril at the hands of the Mafia!
description.8: A special issue putting the spotlight on the Ever Lovin' Blue-Eyed Thing!
description.12: A brand new Marvel vigilante has entered the mix! Meet Hawk-Owl for the very first time!
description.14: There is something suspicious spreading in the city...and it is beyond anything an NYC firefighter has seen before.
description.16: The one-man mutant army goes to Russia with no love!
description.17: What if the heroes of Earth X had to create a new Death?
description.24: A new-reader-friendly beginning! Big changes are coming for the son of Mar-Vell, and you can get in on the ground floor right here...when Cap goes crazy!
description.28: After Alex is shot, he discovers his theme park has been burnt to the ground. Taskmaster becomes jealous with rage after he sees Higashi ask Sandi out. Will Taskmaster take Higashi to task? You bet!
description.29: The Punisher teams up with Wolverine to slaughter some midgets.
description.33: Han Solo'is as skilled, clever, and resourceful as they come, but this time even he may have bitten off more than he can chew. With'Jabba the Hutt'sbounty'on his head, there doesn't seem to be a place in the known galaxies where he can hide for long. But, Han Solo is smart. That's why he comes clean and plans to pay Jabba back what's owed from a botched smuggler's run. Enter a shrewd'Devaronian'with a taste for money that decides Solo's a prize that's too good to pass up. And since this mercenary is working for Jabba directly, it doesn't bode well for Solo and'Chewie. What fate will await them in the dark, odorous prison-depths of Jabba's palace? And what infamous, uninvited guest will drop by and completely alter the chase for the last living'Skywalker?
description.35: Banner is being framed for the murder of a woman he doesn't know -- and the only one that can clear his name is Agent Pratt! Too bad he's preoccupied with killing Banner himself!
description.36: Wolverine rescues a young mutant from an Afghani mutant slave ring and encounters Fantomex. What is the mysterious Frenchman up to this time? Meanwhile, Professor Xavier is made the target of a daring assassination attempt.
description.37: An important'Senate'vote is imminent, and a'Senator'from a small system is suddenly in possession of two things he never expected to have: the power of a "swing" vote, and a death threat! At the insistence of the Supreme Chancellor,'Jedi Knight'Obi-Wan Kenobi'and his'Padawan'Anakin Skywalker'are ordered to help protect the Senator, along with the Senator's regular team of'Senate Guards. Ordinarily, four stalwart protectors would be more than enough to ensure the Senator's safety, but as the'Jedi'and the Guards discover, this situation is far from ordinary!
description.42: After witnessing the murder of a young child, Gunz is haunted by visions of someone crying out for help.
description.43: There is a new Vulture in town and he's looking to stir up some trouble. Spider-Man swings in to save the day from the avian menace! Meanwhile, all of Peter's friends are waiting for him at Harry's, but he's nowhere to be found...
description.45: More terrorists make themselves known to try to take down the Sentinel of Liberty.  Can Cap take down an entire squad of killers by himself?
description.48: "Death of the Black Panther" begins here! How can T'Challa defeat an inoperable brain aneurysm? He can't!
description.50: Some people fight in violent bar brawls. Some people kill bad guys because they hate them. And some people chop the legs off of Mafioso with chainsaws. Those people just made Frank Castle's list.
description.51: THE INHUMANS BREAK FREE! The FF must stop Doctor Doom from wreaking havoc across the globe, and deal with the destroyed barrier that was imprisoning the Inhumans.
description.52: Mark Waid and Mike Wieringo ring in an astonishing new era of the Fantastic Four!
description.56: See Agent Zero's initiation with Weapon X before reading the ongoing series, Weapon X (2002)!
description.57: Before reading Weapon X (2002), learn the secrets and origin of Kane, one of the organization's most enigmatic and dangerous recruits!
description.58: From Morlock child to fully-fledged X-Woman, Marrow is taking yet another unexpected turn! Before reading Weapon X (2002), learn all about Marrow's recruitment with Weapon X!
description.59: Sauron of the Savage Land joins Weapon X! Learn why Karl Lykos is the agency's latest pick, before reading Weapon X (2002)!
description.60: True to his namesake "Wild Child" Kyle Gibney plays by no one's rules. But when Weapon X comes a-knocking (and holds him under custody), will this mutant finally become more man than animal? Find out before reading Weapon X (2002)!
description.62: The Fire Department has dealt with fires that take down massive buildings, but what will they do when they encounter a man made of fire?
description.65: Two of New York City's favorite masked, crime-fighting heroes unite in one action packed issue!
description.66: Blaquesmith gives the Solider his new mission -- head to Russia and find a young girl with remarkable power. But Cable's not the only one trailing her...
description.68: Elektra is struggling to survive in the scorching heat of the Mojave Desert. With an endless loop of memories staining her every thought, will Elektra overcome? Jeremy Locke may have kept her alive, but he must pay- at the end of a blood-drenched sai!
description.75: The Mangaverse will be changed forever as a "take no prisoners" Doctor Doom leaves only corpses in his wake!
description.76: What is the Avenging host and what important role do they play?
description.77: The crazed conclusion to the Green Goblin saga!'
description.79: Tombstone's plan to escape from prison may end up with him laid out and dying.
description.80: The Thing is used as a pawn in the battle of the Kree vs. the Skrulls!
description.81: It's the rootin'-tootin', gun-slingin' conclusion to our weirdest yarn yet! Trapped in the Old West in the 1800's, Black Panther and company find themselves caught in Loki's latest scheme to destroy the Norse Gods! Can T'Challa, the Two-Gun Kid, Rawhide Kid and Kid Colt save the mighty Thor and stop Loki before he brings on the death of the Gods?
description.82: May's life is falling apart and she feels it's all her fault: The Faces duo is wreaking havoc because she let them free, Courtney Duran is in a coma, Spider-Man has a bionic leg. Will Spider-Girl find a way to make up for her previous mistakes?
description.83: Personal issues cause tension within the team, causing major drama between members. Meanwhile, a visit from a rival's lawyer could spell disaster for Venus.
description.86: Spider-Man and Black Cat narrow in on Garrison Klum as Mister Brownstone. Following their suspicion, Felicia decides to surprise Klum at his apartment and finds out his true super-powers...and the reason behind his deadly operation.
description.90: The Fantastic Four race against time as they stop the evil reproductions of the Thing from wreaking havoc across the planet.
description.91: Alex and Outlaw take down some jewelry thieves. Meanwhile, Taskmaster leaves Sandi high and dry. Plus, the introduction of Mary Zero!
description.92: Spider-Man struggles to stay alive under tons of debris, but if he doesn't free himself MJ and her co-workers face certain death at the hands of Doctor Octopus and Carlyle.
description.93: To secure the future of the planet Ryloth, and the continued stability of the Republic, newly-Knighted Jedi Aayla Secura must breech an impenetrable fortress and rescue the young heir of one of Ryloth's ruling clans, while her former teacher, Quinlan Vos, fights a battle to the death against a father-and-son team of Morgukai assassins who are armed with weapons his lightsaber can't stop. It may be true that Jedi don't seek excitement, but excitement has found Quin and Aayla, and it will take every bit of their training to come out of this adventure alive!
description.94: He's bald. He's bad. His'lightsaber'is purple. He's'Mace Windu! Make sure not to miss out on this stunning tribute to the baddest'Jedi Councilmember to ever have his'midi-chlorians'counted!'
description.96: Banner finds himself in a strange city in a stranger's bed, and he can't keep his thoughts together long enough to figure out wants happening. Then when the woman sharing Banner's bed shows up dead in the closet, Agent Pratt maybe the only one with answers.
description.99: A year after his death, Kitty is still trying to recover from the loss of Colossus when she thinks she sees him alive again on the street.

7.text: The battle is over. The X-Men have won. But many of them have been wounded. Who will survive? Featuring Captain America, Iron Man, and The Thing!

9.text: Matt Murdock is going to court, this time as a defendant himself!

10.text: The world's leaders have disappeared, and only the Avengers can guide Earth out of chaos! But the path leads to an extradimensional realm ruled by an unexpected adversary!

13.text: Behold, the birth of the Church of Thor! What does this mean for the Thunder God? Who are his new followers?

15.text: A man who is aflame hijacks an ambulance!

18.text: Tony Stark invents a time-machine and travels back to the land of knights and chivalry. But, a startling discover in the present reveals he may never return. By the wonderful imagination that brought us Warlord.

19.text: She's hit rock bottom- but now Elektra’s fighting back! Will Marvel’s deadliest assassin have the final hit on Jeremy Locke and company?

20.text: Chamber wakes up to bullet holes in his chest. He tracks down and fights a stalker from the anti-mutant hate group, Purity. The Purity agent tells Jono news about the explosion that killed Gigi’s boyfriend.

21.text: This is it! Writer Dan Jolley and artist Greg Scott deliver the good n’ gory conclusion to Sabretooth’s saga! The final fate of Bonnie Hale! The beyond brutal death of the super soldiers! Will Creed and Bonnie find love together once the dust settles?

22.text: Wolverine’s back in Japan! Summoned by the spirit of his beloved Mariko, Logan returns to the Yashida family compound. Waiting for him there is a netsuke left by Mariko, an old-fashioned toggle from the age of the Feudal Samurai. And once Logan picks it up, he’s transported to ancient, 1100s Japan! Read for the breathtakingly gorgeous art and script by George Pratt!

23.text: Continuing the moody, fully-painted adventure! How did Lyle Crawford become ensnared with The Hand, and what precious information does he have against their front man? Elektra does unholy battle against several mystic hosts.

26.text: Dr. Octopus is out for revenge and Kraven the Hunter is out to bag the ultimate prey. Can Spider-Man survive double trouble?

27.text: The critically acclaimed trilogy begins its next installment as we find things in this alternate future timeline not working out as well as some had hoped at the end of Earth X.

30.text: Caught in the heart of a nuclear explosion, mild-mannered scientist Bruce Banner finds himself' during moments of extreme stress' transformed into the walking engine of destruction known as the Incredible Hulk. These stories include the evolution of the grotesque Abomination and the emergence of the gamma-irradiated super-genius known as the Leader.

31.text: This deluxe hardcover volume collects the New X-Men material found in New X-Men Vol. 1: E is for Extinction and New X-Men Vol. 2: Imperial' plus character sketches, story excerpts, scripts and other behind-the-scenes bonus material.

32.text: The first appearances of some of the most popular characters in the title's long run' including G.I. Joe team members Flint, Lady Jaye and Ripcord; and the villainous brothers Tomax and Xamot.

34.text: A vicious murder on Counter-Earth puts Moonstone and Dallas Riordan on the hunt for a psychotic super human. But in order to stop him, will Moonstone repeat the sins of her past? This is THUNDERBOLTS, baby, so the answer is: watch out Phantom Eagle!

36.text: Wolverine rescues a young mutant from an Afghani mutant slave ring and encounters Fantomex. What is the mysterious Frenchman up to this time? Meanwhile, Professor Xavier is made the target of a daring assassination attempt.

Wolverine rescues a young mutant from an Afghani mutant slave ring and encounters Fantomex. What is the mysterious Frenchman up to this time? Meanwhile, Professor Xavier is made the target of a daring assassination attempt.

39.text: While Thor Girl fights soldiers in the rainforest, Perrikus and Adva attack Thor in Asgard with the intention of toppling the Thunder God's regime! Will Thor, with the power of the Bloodaxe, be able to fight them off!

40.text: HELLFIRE AND BRIMSTONE PART 1 A dark vision of a monstrous Phoenix begins to haunt Jean Grey. Plus, the debut of Ultimate Kitty Pryde!

41.text: Explore the history between Nocturne and Thunderbird, and learn of the true fate of their unborn child.

42.text: After witnessing the murder of a young child, Gunz is haunted by visions of someone crying out for help.

43.text: There is a new Vulture in town and he's looking to stir up some trouble. Spider-Man swings in to save the day from the avian menace! Meanwhile, all of Peter's friends are waiting for him at Harry's, but he's nowhere to be found...

There is a new Vulture in town and he's looking to stir up some trouble. Spider-Man swings in to save the day from the avian menace! Meanwhile, all of Peter's friends are waiting for him at Harry's, but he's nowhere to be found...

44.text: Rogue versus Vargas! Can Rogue sustain all the powers she's been juggling around or will everything come crashing down for the Southern belle?

46.text: Vision comes into contact with Victoria Anderson, the granddaughter of Phineas Horton, and receives valuable information on the Gremlins from his creator.

47.text: Camelot Productions and their hired goons represent the latest upset to Kraven’s movie!

49.text: The plot against the Emperor and Darth Vader proceeds, but as the conspirators worry about whether either of their targets suspect, and how much they might suspect, they also begin to wonder about each other. Can the cold-blooded killer Gauer be trusted? What about the ambitious Imperial Officer Dezsetes? And who can tell what goes on behind the blank eyes of the cybernetically enhanced Grand Moff Trachta? In the midst of the plots and counter plots, word comes of a new threat- a new unknown Jedi has emerged to challenge Vader.

54.text: This is it! When Mr. Tune decides to stay behind to finish his masterpiece of evil, it's up to Punisher to shut the madman down! Will the Brothers Grace fall by the end of this issue?

55.text: Mr. Hyde thinks he's tough, and he is - maybe even tough enough to fight the Avengers! But a greater power threatens the Earth itself, which suddenly has a lot fewer people on it!

61.text: Take a trip into Thor's past. Follow the Godling into the valley where Thialfi's destiny intersected with that of the gods! Discover the secrets long thought forgotten!

63.text: Meet Jennifer Montez, a vital member of the EMS. She's used to saving lives, but there are always some she cannot save…

67.text: It's Iron Man's final showdown with Ty. But, in a virtual world where Ty is like a god, it is Tony's mind that will save him.

68.text: Elektra is struggling to survive in the scorching heat of the Mojave Desert. With an endless loop of memories staining her every thought, will Elektra overcome? Jeremy Locke may have kept her alive, but he must pay- at the end of a blood-drenched sai!

69.text: Will new X-Man Chamber solve the mystery of a hate crime — or become the next victim?

70.text: What is the strange attraction between an innocent girl pursued by super humans and her protector, Sabretooth? Could it be... love? Nah! But lust? Definitely!

71.text: As Kearse and Gray dig deeper into mutant subculture, they're forced to confront unpleasant truths -- about themselves!

72.text: Continuing Scott Morse’s fully-painted adventure! Elektra is visited by the dead blues musician who asks her to take the life…of his own son? The mystery continues to unravel as Elektra’s grip over The Hand slips.

74.text: It's the last issue! A major shift in the status quo may leave Rick Jones jilted and alone! Genis “unplugs” Marlo from the memory stealing beings who have plucked her from the Microverse!

78.text: X-Man Kitty Pryde has decided to give up the hero life and enroll at the University of Chicago. Unfortunately, she still lives in a world that hates and fears mutants, and college campuses are no exception.

87.text: LEGACY PART 4 The epic showdown between the Green Goblin and Spider-Man begins! Nick Fury reveals a terrible truth about the nature of the wonder drug called Oz!

88.text: A new team is forged -- but can they survive their first mission?! Why does Harrier harbor a secret hatred towards Hawkeye? And will he decide to act on that anger? This is the THUNDERBOLTS, baby, so the answer is: watch out, Hawkeye!

89.text: The Masters of Evil need to be stopped, but can Songbird and the New Thunderbolts do it without the help of Hawkeye?

95.text: Have Rogue and Gambit truly been slain? And, Khan makes his final all-or-nothing attack run!

98.text: Vision, with the help of Derek, tracks down the descendants of Phineas Horton.
